how do I prevent WSL from appending Windows folders to PATH?

---

<sub>⏱️ 11s</sub>

### 💬 Copilot

To prevent WSL from appending Windows folders to PATH, edit or create `/etc/wsl.conf`:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/wsl.conf
```

Add this configuration:

```ini
[interop]
appendWindowsPath = false
```

Then **restart WSL** from PowerShell/CMD:

```powershell
wsl --shutdown
```

Next time you start WSL, Windows paths won't be in your PATH.

**Alternative - Selective Control:**

If you want some Windows tools but not all paths:

```ini
[interop]
appendWindowsPath = false
```

Then manually add specific Windows tools to your `~/.bashrc` or `~/.zshrc`:

```bash
export PATH="$PATH:/mnt/c/Windows/System32"
```

This gives you full control over which Windows directories are accessible.

